­It was on this bench in 2007 that the notorious artist Tracey Emin surrendered all her art rebel credibility when she decided to become a member of the Royal Academy of Arts"±
®To Baby Angelina
Our Beautiful angel, Our hearts are filled with sorrow for having left us so soon
We love you; Miss you every moment of everyday
Mum. Dad. Sister & Family"³
°This bench and nearby tree
stands in honour of the legendary actor
Jeremy Brett
(1933-1995)
His love, laughter and immense courage
in the face of adversity inspires us all"¶
³SOUTHBANK
CENTRE
Modified Social
Bench NY #5
Jeppe Hein, 2015
Powder-coated aluminium
Supported using public funding by
Supported 
by
ARTS COUNCIL ENGLAND
#SocialBenches"¹
¶THOMAS BRAWLEY 03/08/1919 to 31/12/2009
Beloved husband, father & grandfather. Tommy liked to walk daily
round the Park to observe the seasonal changes unfolding.
We enjoyed many happy family hours in his special place.
A wonderful husband and father with great wit and intelligence
he loved his family dearly and we miss him so much.
AGNES BRAWLEY
20th September 1923 to 22nd of March 2013
Much loved Wife, Mother and Grandmother"؛
·In Loving Memory of
Basil Kenneth Drake
15th March 1931 to 9th April 1998
Who brought his funfairs to the borough for over 40 years
and helped to raise money for various charities"¾
